---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="Automated Multi-Client Delivery | Case Study">
  <div class="case-bg">
    <div class="case-shell">
      <a href="/case-studies" class="back-button">&larr; Back to Case Studies</a>

      <header class="case-header">
        <span class="case-eyebrow">FOUNDATION CASE STUDY &middot; DELIVERY</span>
        <h1>Automating Multi-Client Delivery on Airflow + AWS</h1>
        <p class="case-lede">
          The delivery layer that took daily client transfers off engineering's plate
          entirely &mdash; orchestrated transfers across pharma, life sciences, and RWE buyers
          with per-client SLAs, security models, and schedules. 50+ workflows running daily, no on-call burn.
        </p>
        <div class="case-meta">
          <div class="meta-block"><span class="meta-key">ROLE</span><span class="meta-val">Architect &amp; builder</span></div>
          <div class="meta-block"><span class="meta-key">SCALE</span><span class="meta-val">50+ daily workflows, 8+ clients</span></div>
          <div class="meta-block"><span class="meta-key">STACK</span><span class="meta-val">Airflow (MWAA), Lambda, S3, IAM, EventBridge, Terraform</span></div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="case-section">
        <h2>The problem</h2>
        <p>
          Before this layer existed, every client got their data through a manual process &mdash;
          someone running queries, packaging files, validating outputs, then handing off via SFTP
          or cross-account S3. Each client had different security requirements, different file
          formats, and different schedules. It consumed 40+ hours of engineering time per month
          and broke regularly when somebody forgot a step.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="case-section">
        <h2>What I built</h2>

        <div class="block-grid">
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Standardized transfer DAGs</h3>
            <p>One DAG pattern that any client can plug into: pull from Snowflake, validate, package per client spec, drop to the client's S3 path. New client onboarding is a config change, not a code change.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Cross-account delivery via STS</h3>
            <p>STS AssumeRole for temporary, least-privilege access to client S3 buckets. Scoped IAM policies per client path. Secrets Manager for any credentials that can't ride on IAM.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Per-client lag &amp; schedule awareness</h3>
            <p>Some clients deliver yesterday's date in today's file; some run weekly only on Mondays; some need same-day. Schedules and lag rules encoded in DAG config, not buried in code.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>EventBridge + Lambda triggers</h3>
            <p>EventBridge fires Lambdas on file arrival to send manifests, kick off downstream jobs, and notify ops. Unattended deliveries that confirm themselves end-to-end.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Audit trail by default</h3>
            <p>Every transfer logs row counts, file hashes, and delivery confirmation. Auditors and clients can verify any historical delivery without engineering involvement.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="block">
            <h3>Terraform-managed end-to-end</h3>
            <p>S3 buckets, IAM roles, MWAA environments, EventBridge rules &mdash; all in Terraform. New client onboarding spins up infrastructure deterministically.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="case-section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>This is the layer clients actually see. If delivery fails, the platform fails &mdash; tokenization elegance doesn't matter if the file doesn't land.</li>
          <li>40+ hours/month back to engineering. That's the difference between firefighting deliveries and building the next thing.</li>
          <li>Onboarding a new buyer used to take days of engineering work. Now it's hours, mostly config.</li>
          <li>The orchestration patterns here became the foundation for the V2 tokenization rebuild's per-client chain isolation.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="case-section">
        <h2>What evolved</h2>
        <p>
          This delivery layer ran on Airflow V1. AWS deprecated V1; the migration to MWAA V3 was
          one of the forcing functions for the
          <a href="/case-studies/v2-tokenization-rebuild" class="inline-link">V2 tokenization rebuild</a>.
          Per-client transfer DAGs got rewritten with V3-compatible patterns &mdash; inline DAG definitions,
          updated IAM trust policies across executor ARNs, and idempotent retry semantics that V1 didn't enforce.
        </p>
      </section>

      <div class="case-footer">
        <p>Want to talk about multi-tenant orchestration or healthcare data delivery at scale?</p>
        <div class="footer-buttons">
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-ruffin-a9b767102" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="footer-cta">Connect on LinkedIn</a>
          <a href="/case-studies" class="footer-link">See more case studies &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .case-bg {
      min-height: 100vh;
      background: var(--background-color);
      color: var(--text-color);
      padding: 100px 20px 80px;
    }
    .case-shell { max-width: 880px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .back-button {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--primary-color);
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: opacity 0.3s;
    }
    .back-button:hover { opacity: 0.7; }

    .case-header { margin-bottom: 4rem; }
    .case-eyebrow {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 11px;
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      color: var(--primary-color);
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }
    .case-header h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      line-height: 1.15;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #ffffff 0%, #c8b8e8 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }
    .case-lede {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      font-weight: 300;
    }
    .case-meta {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 16px;
      padding: 20px;
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: 12px;
    }
    .meta-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }
    .meta-key { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.12em; color: var(--primary-color); text-transform: uppercase; }
    .meta-val { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--text-color); font-weight: 500; }

    .case-section { margin-bottom: 3.5rem; }
    .case-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-color);
      margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--card-border);
    }
    .case-section p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    .case-section .inline-link { color: var(--primary-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
    .case-section .inline-link:hover { opacity: 0.75; }
    .bullets { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .bullets li {
      padding: 10px 0 10px 22px;
      position: relative;
      font-size: 0.97rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      line-height: 1.6;
    }
    .bullets li::before {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 18px;
      width: 6px; height: 6px;
      background: var(--primary-color);
      border-radius: 50%;
    }

    .block-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 16px; }
    .block {
      padding: 22px;
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--card-border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      transition: border-color 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
    }
    .block:hover { border-color: rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.3); box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.06); }
    .block h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-color); margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .block p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

    .case-footer {
      margin-top: 4rem;
      padding: 32px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.04) 0%, rgba(124, 58, 237, 0.08) 100%);
      border: 1px solid rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.18);
      border-radius: 14px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .case-footer p { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1.4rem; }
    .footer-buttons { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; }
    .footer-cta {
      padding: 0.85rem 2rem;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #a855f7 0%, #7c3aed 100%);
      color: white;
      border-radius: 10px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      transition: all 0.3s;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 24px var(--primary-glow);
    }
    .footer-cta:hover { transform: translateY(-2px); box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(168, 85, 247, 0.5); }
    .footer-link { color: var(--primary-color); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 500; }
    .footer-link:hover { opacity: 0.7; }

    @media (max-width: 720px) {
      .case-meta { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .block-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>
